longBusinessSummary: ImpediMed Limited, a medical software technology company, together with its subsidiaries, develops, manufactures, and sells bioimpedance spectroscopy (BIS) devices and software services in Australia, North America, and internationally. It offers SOZO, a noninvasive bioimpedance spectroscopy device for the detection of lymphedema and fluid status monitoring of heart failure patients; SFB7, a single-channel, tetrapolar BIS device to analyze body composition in healthy individuals; and ImpediVET, a single-channel, tetrapolar (BIS) device that measures fluid status and tissue composition for veterinary applications. The company sells its devices to hospitals and clinics. ImpediMed Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Pinkenba, Australia.
